label.value: increased RNA level during stress response to zinc ion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular stress response to zinc ions is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: altered protein level during stress response to zinc ion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell differs from normal during a cellular stress response to zinc ions. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein level during cellular response to zinc ion starvation

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. label.value: normal protein level during cellular response to zinc ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to zinc ion starvation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal endosome organization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which  endosome organization is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abnormal post-Golgi vesicle-mediated transport

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of substances via vesicles from the Golgi to other parts of the cell is abnormal..

label.value: abnormal recycling endosome to Golgi transport

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of substances via vesicles from recycling endosomes to the Golgi is abnormal.

label.value: normal protein localization to vacuole

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the vacuole is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to late endosome

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to late endosomes is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased actin filament depolymerization involved in actomyosin contractile ring assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin filament polymerization, i.e. the addition of actin monomers to a filament, occurs to a lower extent than normal as part of contractile ring assembly during cytokinesis.

label.value: normal Arp2/3 complex-mediated actin nucleation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin monomers associate to form a new branch on the side of an existing actin filament, mediated by the Arp2/3 protein complex, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased Atg1/ULK1 kinase complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of Atg1/ULK1 kinase complex assembly is decreased.

label.value: increased 23S rRNA precursor level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any 23S rRNA precursor measured in a cell is higher than normal.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: increased 22S rRNA precursor level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any 22S rRNA precursor measured in a cell is higher than normal.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: 20S rRNA precursor absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 20S rRNA precursor measured in a cell is too low to detect.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: normal 90S preribosome assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the assembly of the 90S preribosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased protein level during stress response to zinc ion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular stress response to zinc ions is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased origin firing efficiency in subtelomeric heterochromatin

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the probability that a DNA replication will initiate at a particular replication origin located in heterochromatin at subtelomeric regions is higher than in wild type. In cells with increased origin firing efficiency, genomic DNA replication initiates from more origins than wild type, and is completed in more, smaller segments, than wild type.

label.value: abnormal ribosomal small subunit assembly

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which assembly of the ribosomal small subunit is abnormal.

label.value: abolished NLS binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which binding to a nuclear localization sequence (NLS) in a protein by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: increased rate of mitotic spindle elongation during anaphase A

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic spindle elongation is increased during anaphase a.

label.value: decreased duration of mitotic anaphase B

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through anaphase B of mitosis is shorter than normal. Anaphase B is the stage of mitosis in which the polar microtubules elongate and the two poles of the spindle move farther apart.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nuclear envelope during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nuclear envelope is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal growth on mycophenolic acid

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing mycophenolic acid.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K14 ubiquitination during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which ubiquitination of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: altered histone H3-K9 methyltransferase substrate specificity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the substrate specificity of a gene product that executes histone H3-K9 specific methyltransferase activity is altered. For example, preference for modified (e.g. ubiquitinated) H3 molecules may be enhanced or diminished.

label.value: abolished ubiquitin binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which binding to ubiquitin by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: normal meiotic cell cycle process

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a cell executes a meiotic cell cycle process normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type). A meiotic cell cycle process is any of the processes that form part of the meiotic cell cycle, and thereby ensures successive accurate and complete genome replication and meiotic chromosome segregation.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: normal initial meiotic spindle pole body separation in meiosis II

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the initial release of duplicated spindle pole bodies that occurs as part of the second meiotic nuclear division, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abnormal initial meiotic spindle pole body separation in meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the initial release of duplicated spindle pole bodies that begins with the nucleation of microtubules from each SPB within the nucleus, and occurs as part of the first meiotic nuclear division, is abnormal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: abolished initial meiotic spindle pole body separation in meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the initial release of duplicated spindle pole bodies that begins with the nucleation of microtubules from each SPB within the nucleus, and normally occurs as part of the first meiotic nuclear division, does not occur.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: normal spindle elongation in meiosis II

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the lengthening of the distance between poles of the meiotic spindle that occurs as part of the second meiotic nuclear division is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: meiotic spindle collapse

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a short meiotic spindle assembles, and may begin elongation, but does not elongate normally or completely, and eventually collapses. Upon collapse the spindle may break or shrink.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to sulfur starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to sulfur starvation is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased RNA level during cellular response to sulfur starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to sulfur starvation is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: elongated vegetative cell during sulfur starvation

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is elongated when the cell is subject to sulfur starvation.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: abolished sporulation during sulfur starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which ascospore formation does not occur when cells are subject to sulfur starvation.

label.value: loss of viability upon sulfur starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable when cells the population are subject to sulfur starvation.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown under glucose-depleted conditions, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon return to conditions supporting vegetative growth is measured and compared to wild type.

label.value: normal cell cycle arrest at mitotic G2/M phase transition during sulfur starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested normally at the mitotic G2/M phase transition when the cell is subject to sulfur starvation.

label.value: abnormal regulation of transcription by nutrient

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of transcription as a consequence of the presence of one or more specific nutrient(s) is abnormal. For example, specific genes that are normally not transcribed in the presence of the nutrient may be transcribed in the mutant, or vice versa.

label.value: increased negative regulation of transcription by zinc

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which negative regulation of transcription by zinc occurs to a greater extent than normal. Specific genes that are normally not transcribed in the presence of zinc ions are not derepressed in the mutant under conditions that derepress transcription in wild type cells.

label.value: increased DNA binding during cellular response to zinc ion

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of DNA binding by a gene product is increased during a cellular response to zinc ions, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: increased level of ribosomal protein gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more RNAs transcribed from genes encoding ribosomal proteins measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells).

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: increased duration of cell fusion during mating

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cells fuse for a longer time than normal during mating.

label.value: increased protein localization to actin fusion focus

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the actin fusion focus is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to actin fusion focus

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the actin fusion focus is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: ectopic actin fusion focus assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which actin fusion focus assembly takes place in one or more abnormal locations. An actin fusion focus normally forms during mating at the site where the two cells will fuse. Ectopic fusion foci often form near actin cortical patches, and may also have abnormal composition.

label.value: normal growth on vanadate

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing vanadate ions (VO4(3-)).

label.value: normal spindle elongation in meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the lengthening of the distance between poles of the meiotic spindle that occurs as part of the first meiotic nuclear division is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
